HOUSE JOINT RESOLUTION 1141
By Reedy
A RESOLUTION to recognize Sheriff Kevin Sugg of Houston
County on the occasion of his retirement.
WHEREAS, it is appropriate that the members of this General Assembly should honor
those citizens who have performed with uncommon devotion and enthusiasm throughout their
careers in law enforcement; and
WHEREAS, Sheriff Kevin Sugg of Houston County is one such estimable individual, who
has devoted his life to the preservation of law and order and the protection of his fellow citizens;
and
WHEREAS, after a thirty-nine-year career in law enforcement, Sheriff Sugg recently
announced that he will take his much-deserved retirement later this year, having devoted twelve
years of his life to public service and law enforcement as sheriff of Houston County; and
WHEREAS, during his career, Kevin Suggs has devoted himself to serving the people of
Houston County, proving himself to be an officer of the highest order; he earned the respect of
his peers and fellow citizens alike for his work ethic, integrity, professionalism, and leadership
skills; and
WHEREAS, as sheriff, he has taken on many improvement projects to make the
Houston County Sheriff's Office and the jail state-of-the-art, including the installation of a new
roof for the jail and a complete repair of the jail's sewer system that included development of a
backup plan if it goes down and the purchase of a backup pump; and
WHEREAS, during his exceptional career in law enforcement, Kevin Sugg has served as
a State Trooper with the Tennessee Highway Patrol and attended three different police
academies, the Tennessee Law Enforcement Academy, the Federal Law Enforcement
Academy, and the Tennessee Highway Patrol Academy, from which he graduated in the top ten
percent of his class; and
