- 1 -

WHEREAS, throughout his many worthy endeavors, Sheriff Sugg has been blessed with
the love and support of his wife, Beth Sugg, who is also retiring from the Houston County
Sheriff's Office, having served with distinction as the department's accountant; and
WHEREAS, keeping busy after their retirements, the Suggs will open a barbeque
restaurant in Erin, Sugg's Barbeque, which will offer delicious food from Sheriff Sugg's collection
of five custom-made ovens on which he has perfected his masterful grilling style; and
WHEREAS, Sheriff Kevin Sugg brought honor to the office of sheriff, a most fitting
station that recognized his devotion to the safety and preservation of his community; and
WHEREAS, Sheriff Sugg exemplifies the values of hard work, compassion, and devotion
to community that are characteristic of a true Tennessean and diligent officer of the law; and
WHEREAS, throughout his estimable career, he demonstrated the utmost
professionalism, ability, and integrity, winning the respect and admiration of his colleagues and
the citizens of Houston County; now, therefore,
BE IT RESOLVED BY THE HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES OF THE ONE HUNDRED
FOURTEENTH GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF THE STATE OF TENNESSEE, THE SENATE
CONCURRING, that we hereby honor Sheriff Kevin Sugg of Houston County on the occasion of
his retirement, commend his many years of distinguished service, and wish him continued
success in all his future endeavors.
BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED, that an appropriate copy of this resolution be prepared
for presentation with this final clause omitted from such copy and upon proper request made to
the appropriate clerk, the language appearing immediately following the State seal appear
without House or Senate designation.
